WEBVTT

00:06.397 --> 00:08.617
male announcer: Previously
on "The Purge"...

00:08.660 --> 00:09.705
- Somebody put a bounty
on your head.

00:09.748 --> 00:10.706
- What have I done
to all of you

00:10.749 --> 00:11.837
to make you
hate me so much?

00:11.881 --> 00:13.187
- You killed my wife.

00:13.230 --> 00:14.753
- I'm sorry.
- Don't leave me!

00:14.797 --> 00:16.146
I couldn't stop thinking

00:16.190 --> 00:17.452
about what happened
on Purge Night.

00:17.495 --> 00:20.324
- It must be hard,
I know Andy was your friend.

00:20.368 --> 00:22.283
- It's sick, Ben.

00:22.326 --> 00:23.284
[shouts indistinctly]

00:23.327 --> 00:24.372
- [screams]

00:25.547 --> 00:26.678
Kelen!

00:26.722 --> 00:28.158
- Shit, Jackals.

00:28.202 --> 00:29.768
- Thieves who steal
from other thieves.

00:29.812 --> 00:31.379
- Tommy Ortiz, come out
with your hands up!

00:31.422 --> 00:32.815
- The banks put the money
in the air.

00:32.858 --> 00:35.252
We can take it before
it ever leaves the ground.

00:35.296 --> 00:36.601
[screens fizzle]
- Jammer's in.

00:37.341 --> 00:38.299
- Me and my guys
will be working

00:38.342 --> 00:39.474
private security that night,

00:39.517 --> 00:40.866
we'll be the ones
guarding the plane.

00:40.910 --> 00:42.172
- I messed with the wrong guys

00:42.216 --> 00:43.304
and I think they're coming
to Purge me.

00:43.347 --> 00:44.740
- Are you okay?

00:44.783 --> 00:47.438
- Esme committed
an act of treason.

00:47.482 --> 00:50.093
This is a priority one manhunt.

00:50.137 --> 00:53.096
- There is something very wrong
and I don't know what to do.

00:53.140 --> 00:54.402
- You can help me.

00:54.445 --> 00:56.839
- So you think you can
take down the NFFA

00:56.882 --> 00:58.710
- They're killing
innocent people off-Purge,

00:58.754 --> 01:00.147
and I think I found the proof.

01:00.190 --> 01:01.844
- The Foundation's gonna wanna
blast it wide.

01:01.887 --> 01:05.456
- I need to help.
Please, just let me stay.

01:08.894 --> 01:11.854
[K. Flay's "This Baby
Don't Cry"]

01:11.897 --> 01:13.769
- ♪ One, two, three

01:13.812 --> 01:15.336
♪

01:15.379 --> 01:17.773
♪ I used to worry
'bout the way that I walk ♪

01:17.816 --> 01:19.557
♪ Like was I talking
too loud? ♪

01:19.601 --> 01:21.733
♪ And could I hang
with the jocks? ♪

01:21.777 --> 01:23.735
♪ I try to tell 'em
See ya later ♪

01:23.779 --> 01:25.215
♪

01:25.259 --> 01:26.782
♪ But they don't wanna
let me go ♪

01:26.825 --> 01:28.305
♪

01:28.349 --> 01:30.351
♪ I send my love
to all the haters ♪

01:30.394 --> 01:31.526
♪

01:31.569 --> 01:33.397
♪ Yeah, I just wanna
let 'em know ♪

01:33.441 --> 01:34.877
♪ This baby don't cry

01:34.920 --> 01:39.751
♪

01:39.795 --> 01:41.405
♪ This baby don't cry

01:41.449 --> 01:46.236
♪

01:46.280 --> 01:48.151
♪ This baby don't cry

01:48.195 --> 01:54.984
♪

01:58.814 --> 02:00.859
♪ This baby don't cry

02:00.903 --> 02:03.427
♪

02:03.471 --> 02:04.559
♪ Cry

02:04.602 --> 02:06.300
♪

02:06.343 --> 02:07.649
♪ Cry

02:07.692 --> 02:11.783
♪

02:11.827 --> 02:13.002
[knocking]

02:13.045 --> 02:15.178
- Mia, I need you
to come downstairs and--

02:15.222 --> 02:16.658
- Dad, get out!

02:18.573 --> 02:20.531
[quiet]
♪ This baby don't cry

02:22.707 --> 02:24.405
Dad,

02:24.448 --> 02:27.712
get out now.

02:30.628 --> 02:32.152
- Okay.

02:34.241 --> 02:35.285
- [laughs]

02:35.329 --> 02:37.287
♪ This baby don't cry

02:37.331 --> 02:38.723
♪

02:38.767 --> 02:40.334
♪ This baby don't cry

02:40.377 --> 02:41.465
[together]
Purge.

02:41.509 --> 02:44.468
[dramatic music]

02:44.512 --> 02:51.432
♪

02:59.918 --> 03:01.311
[gun clicks]

03:05.968 --> 03:06.925
- What's the word?

03:06.969 --> 03:08.797
- It's crazy out there.

03:08.840 --> 03:11.365
Crowds are already forming.

03:11.408 --> 03:13.541
We should allow more time
to move across the city.

03:14.890 --> 03:15.891
- And you?

03:17.588 --> 03:19.634
- What about me?

03:19.677 --> 03:21.853
- Hey, I know that you're
working with these hackers,

03:21.897 --> 03:24.856
and I know you have a score
to settle with the NFFA.

03:24.900 --> 03:27.294
But you've been acting off.

03:27.337 --> 03:28.338
- I'm fine.

03:29.557 --> 03:31.646
- Something I should
know about?

03:35.650 --> 03:37.478
- Don't worry about me.

03:37.521 --> 03:39.044
Okay?
I'll be fine tonight.

03:39.088 --> 03:41.395
Just focus on them,

03:42.309 --> 03:43.397
keeping them safe.

03:45.312 --> 03:46.791
- We get through this,

03:46.835 --> 03:49.316
and we are out
of this country forever.

03:49.359 --> 03:50.969
But we gotta get through
the night.

03:53.755 --> 03:55.365
- It's that time, folks.

03:55.409 --> 03:58.412
- Oh, shit, seriously?
- Man, come on down.

04:00.327 --> 04:01.458
- Let's go.

04:06.333 --> 04:07.159
- What's this?

04:08.335 --> 04:10.467
- It's tradition.
- Tommy's tradition.

04:10.511 --> 04:12.426
- Tommy would be pissed
if we didn't do it.

04:16.125 --> 04:18.954
- [laughs]
- Are you insane?

04:18.997 --> 04:20.738
- Only if we didn't trust
each other.

04:20.782 --> 04:22.174
- We've been doing this
for years.

04:22.218 --> 04:24.525
We've only missed, like, what,
three or four times?

04:24.568 --> 04:25.613
- Five.

04:29.617 --> 04:31.053
- Wait.

04:31.096 --> 04:32.402
Let me.

04:32.446 --> 04:34.448
- [laughing]
Ooh.

04:34.491 --> 04:36.363
This is about to be fun.

04:44.893 --> 04:46.416
- Oh.

04:58.515 --> 04:59.734
[screams]
- Oh, shit!

04:59.777 --> 05:01.431
- Fu--Fu--Oh!
- Oh, shit!

05:01.475 --> 05:02.519
Shit, did I--

05:02.563 --> 05:03.564
- Oh!
I'm just fucking with you.

05:03.607 --> 05:04.695
[all laugh]

05:04.739 --> 05:05.827
- Funny, funny.

05:08.003 --> 05:09.570
- Oh, Tommy would be proud.

05:09.613 --> 05:10.745
- Uh-huh.

05:10.788 --> 05:11.963
- Higgins Boulevard
shut down--

05:12.007 --> 05:13.051
- What's up?

05:13.095 --> 05:15.619
- Ugh.
We have a problem.

05:15.663 --> 05:18.709
Streets around the airport
are closing at 5:00.

05:18.753 --> 05:20.363
- Shit.
What do we gotta do?

05:20.407 --> 05:21.669
- We need access
to those roads

05:21.712 --> 05:23.061
or we can't get the jammer
in range.

05:23.105 --> 05:24.498
- What about the backup jammer,

05:24.541 --> 05:25.890
can you extend the range
on that?

05:25.934 --> 05:28.415
- You built two?
- Just in case.

05:28.458 --> 05:29.981
I can match the frequency
of this controller

05:30.025 --> 05:31.461
with the device
we have on the plane,

05:31.505 --> 05:32.593
but I'm not sure I can
extend the range

05:32.636 --> 05:33.637
without blowing a circuit.

05:33.681 --> 05:36.031
- Ziv, it's Ryan.
We need to talk.

05:36.074 --> 05:37.511
- [sighs]
What do you want?

05:37.554 --> 05:39.034
[indistinct chatter]

05:39.077 --> 05:40.949
- You ever seen crowds
this big?

05:40.992 --> 05:42.646
- Never.

05:42.690 --> 05:45.388
This year is tracking to become
the largest Purge we've seen.

05:45.432 --> 05:46.563
Who are those guys?

05:46.607 --> 05:48.783
- This mask is everywhere.
Big seller.

05:48.826 --> 05:51.829
Everyone wants to be like
The Campus Killer tonight.

05:51.873 --> 05:53.614
They think he's cool.

05:53.657 --> 05:55.485
- With any luck they'll all
get Purged tonight.

05:56.617 --> 05:58.445
Let the citizens
restore the balance.

05:58.488 --> 06:01.665
We don't need people
encouraging off-Purge violence.

06:04.625 --> 06:06.148
Listen.

06:06.191 --> 06:07.802
I know I don't have
to tell you this,

06:07.845 --> 06:10.413
but about Esme,

06:10.457 --> 06:11.936
whatever she was up to,
chances are

06:11.980 --> 06:13.982
she'll make some sort
of move on Purge Night.

06:14.025 --> 06:17.681
Now, if you see her,
don't let it get personal.

06:17.725 --> 06:18.900
Tag like you don't know
her name.

06:18.943 --> 06:21.946
- Not a problem.
She made her choice.

06:21.990 --> 06:23.208
There will be consequences.

06:23.252 --> 06:24.558
- That's right.

06:33.958 --> 06:35.612
- Scanning.

06:36.831 --> 06:37.875
Armed.

06:37.919 --> 06:40.704
- Okay.

06:40.748 --> 06:43.185
Look, Darren,

06:43.228 --> 06:46.057
I just wanted
to say that I was sorry,

06:46.101 --> 06:48.016
I was so distracted
with my own bullshit

06:48.059 --> 06:50.714
that I wasn't there
to protect you.

06:50.758 --> 06:52.586
- Wow.

06:52.629 --> 06:54.152
Gotta be honest,

06:54.196 --> 06:55.893
you haven't really been there
for me the last couple years,

06:55.937 --> 06:57.982
but I guess, in some sort of
messed up way,

06:58.026 --> 06:59.680
this year has been
kinda good for us, huh?

07:01.072 --> 07:02.422
- Except for the fact

07:02.465 --> 07:04.511
that you're on some
America's Most Wanted list.

07:04.554 --> 07:06.251
- Maybe I deserved it.

07:06.295 --> 07:09.037
Look, they had me betray
someone who really trusted me

07:09.080 --> 07:10.952
and I did that.

07:10.995 --> 07:13.520
- It was the system
that betrayed us.

07:13.563 --> 07:16.000
We're supposed to buy
into these laws all year

07:16.044 --> 07:18.046
and just forget about it
for one night.

07:18.089 --> 07:21.484
Who do you think that serves?
Not you.

07:21.528 --> 07:23.530
Not me,
that's for damn sure.

07:23.573 --> 07:25.532
Son, no,
we don't deserve this.

07:26.881 --> 07:27.969
You hear me?

07:29.318 --> 07:30.885
- Aw, hell yeah.

07:30.928 --> 07:33.104
I like this new you, Dad.

07:33.148 --> 07:34.497
Yeah.
- Well,

07:34.541 --> 07:37.108
no matter
what happens tonight,

07:37.152 --> 07:39.676
I promise
I'ma keep you safe.

07:39.720 --> 07:41.852
- Nah, I know that.

07:50.600 --> 07:52.210
[indistinct chatter]

07:52.820 --> 07:55.257
- Double or nothing,
man!

07:55.300 --> 07:56.780
- Yeah, yeah.
- Yeah.

07:56.824 --> 07:58.042
That shit is sick.

07:58.086 --> 08:01.045
- Yo, yo, check out
this TikTok.

08:01.089 --> 08:02.612
It's a Purge confessional.

08:02.656 --> 08:04.005
We're totally making one.

08:05.093 --> 08:07.530
- It's cool.
- Yo!

08:07.574 --> 08:09.924
Does anyone remember
what tonight is?

08:09.967 --> 08:11.621
Or none of you care about
keeping this house safe.

08:11.665 --> 08:13.536
- Turner, chill, man,
we have time.

08:13.580 --> 08:15.233
- Dude, half our preppy
douchebags went home

08:15.277 --> 08:16.626
to hide
with their parents.

08:16.670 --> 08:17.845
We're low on manpower.

08:17.888 --> 08:19.803
- Fine, I'll help.

08:19.847 --> 08:21.805
But, I mean, why don't you
make Ben help, too?

08:21.849 --> 08:23.111
- Have you checked on him?

08:23.154 --> 08:24.982
- Where is he?
- Upstairs.

08:25.026 --> 08:26.636
Still locked in his room.

08:26.680 --> 08:28.899
- He's been
acting weird, man.

08:28.943 --> 08:30.945
- He's seen a lot of off-Purge
death this year

08:30.988 --> 08:33.164
and now it's actual Purge.

08:33.208 --> 08:34.818
So you'd be weird, too.

08:34.862 --> 08:37.560
- I'm just tellin' you,
I'm not looking forward

08:37.604 --> 08:39.867
to spending the night in here
alone with that guy.

08:39.910 --> 08:41.999
- Ben is fine, he's just
sad about his girlfriend.

08:42.043 --> 08:43.740
- That was
two months ago.

08:43.784 --> 08:44.872
- Hey.

08:46.961 --> 08:49.006
I don't think
he's sad anymore, man.

08:49.050 --> 08:50.747
Just go check it out.

08:54.229 --> 08:57.188
[King Gizzard and the Lizard
Wizard's "Self-Immolate"]

08:57.232 --> 08:59.582
♪

08:59.626 --> 09:02.019
- ♪ I have gone insane-o

09:02.063 --> 09:05.066
♪ I lust for volcano

09:05.109 --> 09:08.112
♪ Be with molten lava

09:08.156 --> 09:10.985
♪ Give me my nirvana

09:11.028 --> 09:13.727
♪ I have no vertigo

09:13.770 --> 09:16.686
♪ I lust for tornado

09:16.730 --> 09:19.602
♪ Be a leaf upon air

09:19.646 --> 09:23.301
♪ Venusian mal de mer

09:34.965 --> 09:36.706
- Whoa.

09:36.750 --> 09:38.186
You joining the army
or something?

09:39.753 --> 09:42.886
Yo, when'd you get that?

09:42.930 --> 09:45.672
And why?
- Going out tonight.

09:45.715 --> 09:48.762
- Dude, are you serious?

09:51.808 --> 09:53.288
Think about
what happened last year.

09:54.419 --> 09:56.900
- Last year you pissed yourself
and ran away.

10:00.121 --> 10:02.297
- Look, I know you're trying
to push people away,

10:02.340 --> 10:04.168
'cause I did the same thing
when my brother died.

10:04.212 --> 10:06.170
Just 'cause Kelen is gone
doesn't mean

10:06.214 --> 10:07.998
that you have to
check out like I did.

10:08.042 --> 10:10.000
Could you just stay, man?

10:15.049 --> 10:16.790
- Why are we stopping?

10:16.833 --> 10:20.097
- I think we got a flat.
Can you check your side?

10:20.141 --> 10:21.925
- All right, yeah, sure.

10:32.327 --> 10:35.330
Um, yeah, I don't see anything.

10:36.940 --> 10:38.115
- Right there.
What about that?

10:38.159 --> 10:40.030
Is that a nail?
- Where?

10:42.163 --> 10:43.947
I--I still don't see anything.

10:45.514 --> 10:46.820
[screams]

10:48.604 --> 10:49.910
- [screams]

10:49.953 --> 10:52.913
[grunting and yelping]

10:52.956 --> 10:55.176
Yo, what the hell
are you doing?

10:55.219 --> 10:56.743
- Son, I didn't know
how else to do it.

10:56.786 --> 10:58.266
- Are you crazy?

10:58.309 --> 11:00.181
- There's no other place
that would keep you safe,

11:00.224 --> 11:01.182
except the hospital.

11:01.225 --> 11:02.792
- How is this keeping me safe?

11:02.836 --> 11:04.838
- Angry neighbors is one thing,

11:04.881 --> 11:07.449
but we're talking
about the NFFA here, okay?

11:07.492 --> 11:10.234
My Purge security is not gonna
stop the government.

11:10.278 --> 11:12.410
- So you break my arm?

11:12.454 --> 11:14.630
- I'm gonna take you
to the hospital.

11:14.674 --> 11:17.328
It's off limits on Purge,
even for them,

11:17.633 --> 11:20.244
There's no way
that they will let you in

11:20.288 --> 11:22.333
without a real injury.

11:23.770 --> 11:26.294
Okay?
That's the only way.

11:26.337 --> 11:27.861
You gotta believe me.

11:30.559 --> 11:31.691
Just stay right there.

11:37.392 --> 11:40.177
Come on, let me brace it.

11:40.221 --> 11:44.399
Son, this is how
you stay alive.

11:57.020 --> 11:59.283
- Is that who I think it is?

11:59.327 --> 12:01.503
- Ziv, I'd like to have
your team stay on point.

12:01.546 --> 12:02.896
- Ease up, Reynolds.

12:02.939 --> 12:05.637
Come on, what do we got?

12:05.681 --> 12:08.205
- I'm here, which gives me
a clear shot

12:08.249 --> 12:09.337
to this access
road which runs

12:09.380 --> 12:10.904
along the edge of the airport.

12:10.947 --> 12:13.515
When I get within range,
I activate the jammer

12:13.558 --> 12:16.344
which keeps the plane grounded
until Purge sirens.

12:16.387 --> 12:18.520
Ziv, you and your team
are here on the tarmac,

12:18.563 --> 12:19.956
guarding the plane.

12:20.000 --> 12:21.523
- Sara and I are here,

12:21.566 --> 12:24.221
ready to smash the barrier
fence when the sirens go off.

12:24.265 --> 12:25.701
As soon as it's legal,
we all drive through,

12:25.745 --> 12:27.094
and we load up the vehicle
together.

12:27.137 --> 12:29.836
- Jammer is the part that
has to be perfectly timed.

12:29.879 --> 12:32.360
Too late and the plane is
already in the air,

12:32.403 --> 12:34.536
too early and the banks
have enough time

12:34.579 --> 12:36.146
to initiate their plan B,

12:36.190 --> 12:38.453
moving the money via ground
transport to God knows where.

12:38.496 --> 12:39.846
- Okay, so what's the problem?

12:39.889 --> 12:41.978
- NFFA is sending
in reinforcements.

12:42.022 --> 12:44.676
- Extra security will be
blocking those access roads.

12:44.720 --> 12:46.722
- Which means that I can't get
within range

12:46.766 --> 12:48.245
to keep the plane grounded.

12:48.289 --> 12:49.420
- Give me the remote.

12:49.464 --> 12:51.292
I'll activate the jammer
from the tarmac.

12:51.335 --> 12:52.554
- Yeah,
that's not gonna happen

12:52.597 --> 12:53.773
because that's the only thing
keeping you

12:53.816 --> 12:54.904
from cutting
us out.

12:54.948 --> 12:56.036
Or worse.

12:56.079 --> 12:57.733
- So what?

12:57.777 --> 12:58.865
We abandon the plan?

12:58.908 --> 13:00.518
- No, you call in a favor,

13:00.562 --> 13:03.608
you get the NFFA to move their
security detail a block over.

13:05.306 --> 13:06.698
- I can't risk it.

13:06.742 --> 13:08.657
I make that call,
it traces back to me.

13:08.700 --> 13:10.615
- Then we're fucked.

13:10.659 --> 13:11.747
- Maybe not.

13:15.577 --> 13:17.622
I have an idea.

13:27.981 --> 13:31.506
- Hey, did you do it?
- Yeah.

13:31.549 --> 13:33.508
- And he made it
to the hospital okay?

13:34.509 --> 13:35.727
- He's safe.

13:37.381 --> 13:40.863
Oh, man,
I think he hates me.

13:40.907 --> 13:42.734
- He might.

13:42.778 --> 13:45.085
But he'll live
to forgive you one day.

13:45.128 --> 13:47.087
And that's what's important.

13:47.130 --> 13:48.740
What you did was brave.

13:50.133 --> 13:51.308
Come here.

13:54.659 --> 13:56.661
Are you sure you're okay
in that house?

13:56.705 --> 13:58.881
You and Michelle, you can come
and hide out here with us.

13:58.925 --> 14:00.535
- No.

14:00.578 --> 14:02.058
I gotta stand up
to these people

14:02.102 --> 14:03.799
or they'll never stop.

14:03.843 --> 14:07.107
- I just hate the thought
of the two of you alone.

14:07.150 --> 14:10.327
Because you gotta stay alive,
Marcus.

14:10.371 --> 14:14.114
For our boy,
and for all of us.

14:14.157 --> 14:16.507
Okay?

14:16.551 --> 14:19.510
[power tools buzzing]

14:19.554 --> 14:20.772
- I knew we should have
started this earlier.

14:20.816 --> 14:22.687
This crack job is not gonna
keep us alive.

14:26.778 --> 14:28.650
Hey, come on, guys, who had
the second floor?

14:28.693 --> 14:29.999
It's only half done.

14:30.043 --> 14:31.435
- Ben said he'd take care of
it.

14:31.479 --> 14:32.436
- So why didn't he?

14:32.480 --> 14:34.438
- Homeboy is freaking me out.

14:34.482 --> 14:35.700
Did you see what he did
to his head?

14:35.744 --> 14:36.963
- Yeah, he cut his hair.
So what?

14:37.006 --> 14:39.443
- Turner, Ben's been acting
weirder than weird,

14:39.487 --> 14:41.054
and I think you just
don't want to see it.

14:43.621 --> 14:46.494
[foreboding music]

14:46.537 --> 14:49.932
♪

14:49.976 --> 14:51.151
- Yo, Ben!

14:51.194 --> 14:52.804
[muffled]
Ben, you up here?

15:11.649 --> 15:13.042
Listening to
a fucking freshman.

15:13.086 --> 15:14.914
Get your shit together.

15:37.066 --> 15:40.026
[foreboding music]

15:40.069 --> 15:47.076
♪

16:05.051 --> 16:07.053
[indistinct chatter]

16:08.184 --> 16:11.187
[phone vibrating]

16:24.070 --> 16:26.028
- Hey, you're leaving
the floor?

16:26.072 --> 16:28.683
- Uh, yeah, I thought I'd grab
a coffee before lockdown.

16:28.726 --> 16:30.250
- We have coffee here.

16:30.293 --> 16:31.425
- Have you tasted it?

16:31.468 --> 16:32.513
- Fair enough.

16:32.556 --> 16:34.341
- Want anything?
- No, I'm good.

16:34.384 --> 16:36.082
Just get back safe.

16:36.125 --> 16:37.126
- Yep.

16:40.260 --> 16:42.218
[car horns honking]

17:05.676 --> 17:07.591
What's going on?
what's wrong?

17:07.635 --> 17:10.072
- Hey, I need another favor.

17:10.116 --> 17:12.422
- I can't.
Curtis is all over me.

17:12.466 --> 17:14.120
- Do you think he knows
you've been helping me?

17:14.163 --> 17:15.991
- No, I don't think so.
No.

17:16.035 --> 17:18.211
- Okay, so I can still
count on you tonight.

17:18.254 --> 17:19.342
- Yes, you can.

17:19.386 --> 17:21.214
- Good.
- We should get moving.

17:22.432 --> 17:26.175
- Wait, he doesn't know,
does he?

17:26.219 --> 17:29.222
- He knows that I'm working
with The Foundation,

17:29.265 --> 17:32.225
he just doesn't know
the endgame.

17:32.268 --> 17:33.400
- [quietly]
Well, why didn't you tell him?

17:33.443 --> 17:35.097
You said he was
a good person.

17:35.141 --> 17:36.229
- He is.

17:36.272 --> 17:38.100
That's why
he would try to stop me.

17:39.188 --> 17:41.103
Do you think you can do him
a favor, this time?

17:41.147 --> 17:43.366
- No,
I cannot get caught, Esme.

17:43.410 --> 17:44.411
- This is different.

17:44.454 --> 17:48.241
Before Purge, I want you
to tag me.

17:48.284 --> 17:49.633
- What?
That is suicide.

17:49.677 --> 17:52.506
- No, I'm talking about
a false hit.

17:55.639 --> 17:57.250
- Where do you wanna
get pinged?

17:57.293 --> 17:59.687
- Okay, five blocks
from the airport.

17:59.730 --> 18:03.995
Create a fake spotting exactly
15 minutes before the sirens.

18:04.039 --> 18:05.475
- I'll need
a believable visual.

18:05.519 --> 18:06.998
- Find one.

18:07.042 --> 18:08.435
- Fine, I'll do it.

18:08.478 --> 18:09.436
- Thank you.

18:09.479 --> 18:10.959
Thank you for all of this.

18:11.002 --> 18:13.048
- I don't mean to interrupt,
but we're running out of time.

18:16.660 --> 18:18.488
- Just stay safe, okay?

18:18.532 --> 18:19.576
For me?

18:19.620 --> 18:21.752
- I'll try.
Thank you.

18:25.278 --> 18:26.409
- Let's go.

18:32.633 --> 18:34.765
- Hey.

18:34.809 --> 18:36.158
- Hey.

18:37.203 --> 18:39.074
What's this?

18:39.118 --> 18:42.382
- There's still time.
Come sit.

18:42.425 --> 18:43.557
- [chuckles]

18:43.600 --> 18:47.735
You did not cook
the night before Purge.

18:48.692 --> 18:52.261
- We had sushi
on our first date, remember?

18:52.305 --> 18:54.611
- Yeah, where do you think
I stopped before I came home?

18:57.875 --> 19:02.445
- So you remember
that place was nasty?

19:03.577 --> 19:05.622
- I went there with you;
you said it was perfect.

19:09.235 --> 19:13.195
- So if this is
our last meal...

19:14.544 --> 19:16.329
We should clear the air.

19:17.721 --> 19:18.722
- I agree.

19:19.854 --> 19:21.551
I hate your mother.

19:22.726 --> 19:24.075
- Oh, really?

19:25.207 --> 19:28.297
- I mean, just, like,
the sound of her voice is--

19:28.341 --> 19:30.473
it's like a fork
in the garbage disposal.

19:30.517 --> 19:32.301
- Damn.

19:33.607 --> 19:35.696
Okay.

19:37.132 --> 19:41.832
The teeth on just that one side
of your mouth are crooked.

19:42.529 --> 19:44.226
It's so weird.

19:44.270 --> 19:45.271
- Wow, that's cold, babe.

19:45.314 --> 19:47.751
- It's like "ugh."

19:47.795 --> 19:50.145
- Hey, really?
Are you serious?

19:50.189 --> 19:52.191
- [laughs]

19:52.234 --> 19:53.844
No.

19:53.888 --> 19:55.803
- Wow.
Wow.

19:55.846 --> 19:57.457
When did you become
so funny?

19:58.849 --> 20:01.243
- I've always been funny.

20:01.287 --> 20:06.248
- Well, this is to a hell
of a year.

20:06.292 --> 20:07.597
- And to us.

20:11.645 --> 20:13.734
- That's worth fighting for.

20:13.777 --> 20:18.695
- Marcus, we have both
screwed up big-time.

20:18.739 --> 20:20.436
We've hurt each other.

20:20.480 --> 20:24.397
It's gonna take time,
but if we get through tonight,

20:24.440 --> 20:28.183
all I can promise is
that I will try every day.

20:31.317 --> 20:33.667
- Me too.

20:42.806 --> 20:44.634
- Who's going hunting
with me tonight?

20:48.638 --> 20:50.292
- Ben, what is this?

20:51.424 --> 20:53.208
Why did you draw all this?

20:53.252 --> 20:55.166
- Why the hell are you
going through my stuff?

20:56.690 --> 20:57.778
- I'm worried about you.

20:57.821 --> 20:59.170
- [laughs]

20:59.214 --> 21:01.303
Fuck off.

21:01.347 --> 21:03.305
- I don't think you're right
in the head, man.

21:03.349 --> 21:04.959
We've all noticed.

21:05.002 --> 21:07.962
You're grieving
and you're angry,

21:08.005 --> 21:10.225
and going out
and purging tonight

21:10.269 --> 21:11.618
isn't gonna help you,

21:11.661 --> 21:14.316
- You don't know what the hell
you're talking about.

21:14.360 --> 21:15.491
- What are you doi--

21:15.535 --> 21:17.624
- Don't touch me.

21:17.667 --> 21:19.234
- Ah, ah, ah!

21:19.278 --> 21:20.714
- Dude.
- Fuck off, Ben, let him go.

21:20.757 --> 21:21.932
- Ah, you're hurting me.

21:21.976 --> 21:24.892
[painful yelps]

21:24.935 --> 21:27.242
- You look like Andy
when he died.

21:30.332 --> 21:32.943
- So sick of this shit,
you fucking psycho.

21:32.987 --> 21:35.468
[both grunting]

21:37.383 --> 21:38.732
- Everyone back away
from him.

21:41.517 --> 21:42.649
- I dare you.

21:44.694 --> 21:46.305
- Just go.

21:47.480 --> 21:48.698
- Do you want me to die?

21:50.961 --> 21:52.789
- You're not giving me
a choice anymore.

21:55.618 --> 21:56.619
- Hey, Turner...

21:58.012 --> 22:02.233
What if I was going out
on Purge to have some fun...

22:04.453 --> 22:07.891
But the dickheads I live with
decided to piss me off instead?

22:12.722 --> 22:15.334
[whispering]
What do you think I'd do?

22:19.860 --> 22:22.819
[spooky music]

22:22.863 --> 22:26.475
♪

22:26.519 --> 22:28.347
Just do it.

22:37.399 --> 22:38.705
That's what I thought.

22:38.748 --> 22:40.402
- Someone open the front door.

22:40.446 --> 22:41.882
- Now, go!
- All right.

22:45.886 --> 22:47.757
- Some brotherhood.

22:58.681 --> 23:00.074
[line trilling]

23:00.117 --> 23:02.555
- We're sorry; all police
and emergency services

23:02.598 --> 23:04.034
have been suspended
in anticipation

23:04.078 --> 23:05.427
of the annual Purge.
If you are still alive--

23:05.471 --> 23:06.602
- Ah, shit.

23:07.821 --> 23:09.649
Get the door secured, now.

23:09.692 --> 23:11.607
- What'd he say to you?
What happened?

23:12.826 --> 23:15.872
- Whatever happens,
whatever he says,

23:15.916 --> 23:18.484
do not let him
back in this house.

23:21.269 --> 23:24.228
[indistinct chatter]

23:33.150 --> 23:36.110
[suspenseful music]

23:36.153 --> 23:43.160
♪

23:52.343 --> 23:53.388
- Ryan, you in place?

23:53.432 --> 23:54.433
- First team set.

23:55.216 --> 23:57.131
Second team's ready to go
as well.

24:06.140 --> 24:09.404
Give the NFFA hell for me,
okay?

24:09.448 --> 24:12.015
Hey, be safe.

24:36.475 --> 24:37.780
- Good luck.

24:37.824 --> 24:39.129
- You too.

24:43.220 --> 24:46.180
[solemn music]

24:46.223 --> 24:50.358
♪

24:50.401 --> 24:52.795
- You know what you gotta do.
Get outta here.

25:00.586 --> 25:03.545
[motorcycle engine roaring]

25:26.133 --> 25:29.092
[foreboding music]

25:29.136 --> 25:36.143
♪

25:38.058 --> 25:41.061
[doorbell chimes]

25:42.541 --> 25:44.194
- It's still early.

25:54.640 --> 25:56.424
[door beeps and thuds]

26:10.177 --> 26:11.308
Hey, what's going on?

26:11.352 --> 26:13.354
- Hey, can we--
- Come in.

26:13.397 --> 26:15.008
- Thanks.
- Is everything okay?

26:15.051 --> 26:16.487
- Yeah, we're fine,

26:16.531 --> 26:18.489
we just didn't want you guys
to go through this alone.

26:19.969 --> 26:21.318
- But what about your place?

26:21.362 --> 26:23.973
- M, a lot of folks are
standing strong together.

26:24.017 --> 26:25.366
They'll be fine without us.

26:25.409 --> 26:27.324
- Wow,
we appreciate this so much.

26:27.368 --> 26:28.456
- Of course.

26:28.499 --> 26:30.589
We shoulda reached out
a long time ago.

26:31.981 --> 26:33.417
Family's gotta stick together.

26:33.461 --> 26:35.071
- Yeah.

26:37.160 --> 26:40.076
[indistinct chatter]

26:40.120 --> 26:42.470
- Okay, Esme, here we go.

26:44.254 --> 26:45.908
[computer chirps]

26:45.952 --> 26:48.171
- Units at airport,
tagged suspect nearby.

26:48.215 --> 26:49.999
Proceed to coordinates.

26:53.089 --> 26:56.092
[sirens blaring]

27:01.315 --> 27:02.403
- Good work.

27:02.446 --> 27:04.448
They're clearing
the access roads.

27:06.276 --> 27:07.451
- Thank Esme.

27:12.195 --> 27:15.155
[dramatic music]

27:15.198 --> 27:21.509
♪

27:21.552 --> 27:22.641
What are you doing here?

27:24.207 --> 27:27.036
- I'm just gonna make sure
you don't get into any trouble.

27:27.080 --> 27:29.343
- Ziv, what is this bullshit?

27:29.386 --> 27:31.084
- Relax, he's there to help.

27:31.127 --> 27:32.607
- Yeah, Ryan.

27:32.651 --> 27:34.261
What can I do to help?

27:40.484 --> 27:42.008
- Scott.

27:42.051 --> 27:43.139
Go take a pass upstairs,
all right?

27:43.183 --> 27:44.358
Make sure all the windows
are secure.

27:44.401 --> 27:45.402
- Okay.

27:46.708 --> 27:48.275
- Hey, Zane, you wanna watch
the front door?

28:23.179 --> 28:26.139
[eerie music]

28:26.182 --> 28:33.189
♪

28:48.291 --> 28:51.251
[thrilling electronic music]

28:51.294 --> 28:55.777
♪

28:57.866 --> 28:59.476
[muffled thump]

29:00.826 --> 29:02.131
- Scott.

29:05.134 --> 29:07.049
Did he come back down?

29:07.093 --> 29:09.095
- Yeah.
- Are you sure?

29:10.226 --> 29:11.837
- Yeah, I guess.

29:11.880 --> 29:14.187
- Yeah, you guess.

29:20.933 --> 29:22.586
Scott.

29:22.630 --> 29:23.979
Scott!

29:32.074 --> 29:34.207
Dude, answer me.

29:34.250 --> 29:35.208
[door clicks]

29:35.251 --> 29:36.905
- Whoa.

29:38.341 --> 29:39.603
- Have you seen Scott?

29:39.647 --> 29:40.779
- I think I heard him
in your room.

29:47.611 --> 29:49.048
[muffled shouting]

29:51.267 --> 29:54.096
[muffled yelps]

29:57.230 --> 29:58.840
- What are you doing?

29:58.884 --> 30:00.842
[muffled voice continues]

30:02.017 --> 30:04.150
What the hell are you doing,
man?

30:10.896 --> 30:13.115
[arrow thwips]

30:14.813 --> 30:16.553
Oh, shit.

30:20.731 --> 30:23.691
[foreboding music]

30:23.734 --> 30:27.608
♪

30:27.651 --> 30:30.176
[both grunting]

30:30.219 --> 30:33.222
[gasping]

30:34.223 --> 30:35.703
[muffled frightened yelps]

30:35.746 --> 30:38.749
[gasping slows]

30:44.755 --> 30:46.322
[muffled yelping]

31:00.423 --> 31:01.729
- You coming?

31:01.772 --> 31:03.078
- It's early.

31:03.122 --> 31:04.253
- What, are you gonna wait

31:04.297 --> 31:05.733
for the security guards
to come back?

31:05.776 --> 31:07.735
Let's get past the checkpoint
before it's too late.

31:07.778 --> 31:08.736
[gun clicks]

31:08.779 --> 31:09.911
- I said wait.

31:09.955 --> 31:11.695
- Or what, ya gonna kill me
before Purge?

31:13.741 --> 31:14.742
- Mo--

31:21.836 --> 31:24.099
[tires squeal]

31:27.276 --> 31:30.105
- Getting close now.
Minutes away.

31:31.019 --> 31:33.979
[dramatic music]

31:34.022 --> 31:38.809
♪

31:38.853 --> 31:40.986
- Ryan, that you?
Come in.

31:41.029 --> 31:43.075
It's too soon.
It's too soon.

31:44.293 --> 31:45.381
[gadget beeps]

31:46.078 --> 31:48.210
[machinery grows quiet]

31:57.306 --> 31:59.265
- Something's wrong.
The controls are fried!

32:01.397 --> 32:02.746
- Ryan, the jammer
went off early.

32:02.790 --> 32:04.226
What the hell did you do?
Come in.

32:05.271 --> 32:06.707
God damn it.

32:06.750 --> 32:08.404
They're gonna unload the safes
from the planes.

32:09.231 --> 32:10.972
The banks are moving the money
across the ground.

32:11.016 --> 32:12.452
Ryan fucked it up.

32:12.495 --> 32:14.280
Ryan, what the hell
are you up to.

32:14.323 --> 32:16.108
Where the hell are you?

32:16.151 --> 32:18.110
- What did you do?
What did you do?

32:18.806 --> 32:21.113
[tires squealing]

32:21.156 --> 32:23.985
[dramatic music]

32:24.029 --> 32:30.992
♪

32:34.082 --> 32:35.170
[grunts]

32:35.214 --> 32:37.781
- [shouting]

32:43.962 --> 32:45.789
[engine revving]

32:45.833 --> 32:49.706
- [grunting]

32:49.750 --> 32:50.794
- Don't do it.

32:51.491 --> 32:54.189
[engine revving]

32:56.235 --> 32:57.323
[car door crunches]

32:57.366 --> 32:58.454
[glass shatters]

32:58.498 --> 33:00.369
[tires screech]

33:10.205 --> 33:13.165
[clock ticking rapidly]

33:13.208 --> 33:16.037
[ominous tone]

33:24.959 --> 33:26.178
- This is not a test.

33:26.221 --> 33:28.876
This is your emergency
broadcast system

33:28.919 --> 33:31.922
announcing the commencement--
- Come on, keep playing.

33:31.966 --> 33:33.185
- Of the annual Purge
sanctioned

33:33.228 --> 33:34.708
by the U.S. government.
- It's a party.

33:34.751 --> 33:36.188
- Weapons of class four--
- Drink, have a good time.

33:36.231 --> 33:37.406
- And lower
have been authorized

33:37.450 --> 33:39.539
for use during the Purge.

33:39.582 --> 33:41.845
- Loading the last one now.

33:41.889 --> 33:42.890
- All other weapons
are restricted.

33:42.933 --> 33:44.065
- Ryan.

33:44.109 --> 33:45.371
Grant.
Shit.

33:45.414 --> 33:46.894
- Government officials
of ranking ten

33:46.937 --> 33:48.330
have been granted immunity--
- The fuck are you up to?

33:48.374 --> 33:50.985
- from the Purge
and shall not be harmed.

33:51.029 --> 33:53.161
- Tap on the windows, guys,
we gotta delay these trucks

33:53.205 --> 33:55.294
till the sirens go off
or we are not getting paid.

33:55.337 --> 33:58.427
- Commencing at the siren,
all crime, including murder--

33:58.471 --> 33:59.950
- Well, get ready.

33:59.994 --> 34:02.910
- will be legal for 12
continuous hours.

34:02.953 --> 34:06.087
Police, fire, and
emergency medical services

34:06.131 --> 34:07.436
will be unavailable

34:07.480 --> 34:09.917
until tomorrow morning
at 7:00 a.m.--

34:09.960 --> 34:11.049
- Listen up.

34:11.092 --> 34:12.441
Another Purge is
about to begin.

34:12.485 --> 34:14.356
Remember, there's a tagged
suspect on the loose.

34:14.400 --> 34:15.488
[claps]

34:15.531 --> 34:17.098
Stay focused.
Let's do this, people.

34:17.142 --> 34:20.449
- Blessed be our New Founding
Fathers and America.

34:20.493 --> 34:22.582
- Open up!
- A nation reborn.

34:22.625 --> 34:24.105
- We have a problem.
I need to reroute you.

34:24.149 --> 34:25.150
Open the door.

34:25.193 --> 34:26.412
[sirens wail]

34:26.455 --> 34:27.978
- Hey, let's get 'em open.

34:28.588 --> 34:29.806
- Let's go.

34:32.940 --> 34:34.463
- Keep playing.

34:36.161 --> 34:37.162
- I'm sorry.

34:40.991 --> 34:42.906
- I need you to open--

34:42.950 --> 34:43.907
Jackals.

34:43.951 --> 34:46.258
[dramatic music]

34:47.520 --> 34:49.087
[gunshot]

34:50.305 --> 34:51.828
[gunshot]

34:57.660 --> 34:58.879
[guns firing rapidly]

34:58.922 --> 35:00.228
[indistinct speech]

35:00.272 --> 35:02.448
[gunfire]

35:02.491 --> 35:03.753
- Watch out!

35:05.755 --> 35:07.366
[indistinct shouting]

35:07.409 --> 35:09.585
[gunfire]

35:09.629 --> 35:11.326
- Cover fire!

35:15.287 --> 35:16.505
- Better get down!

35:17.593 --> 35:18.768
- [groans]

35:19.987 --> 35:22.859
[foreboding music]

35:22.903 --> 35:27.734
♪

35:27.777 --> 35:30.040
- Oh, come on, please.

35:30.084 --> 35:33.305
Please, man, please, come on.

35:33.348 --> 35:34.436
Come on, please.

35:34.480 --> 35:35.916
Please don't--don't make me,
I don't--

35:35.959 --> 35:37.265
- It's okay, dude.

35:38.875 --> 35:40.703
Just drink it.

35:54.978 --> 35:55.979
[arrow thwips]

35:56.023 --> 36:00.027
- Oh, oh.
Oh.

36:00.070 --> 36:01.637
- You fucking psycho!

36:03.813 --> 36:04.988
Untie me!

36:08.122 --> 36:09.993
- Shithead.
- [growls]

36:12.518 --> 36:14.650
[grunting]

36:14.694 --> 36:17.131
- [breathing frantically]

36:17.175 --> 36:18.306
[body thuds]

36:22.484 --> 36:24.312
- Ugh!
- [yelps]

36:29.796 --> 36:31.798
- Hey.

36:31.841 --> 36:33.756
- [gargles and spurts]

36:33.800 --> 36:34.801
Oh.

36:40.110 --> 36:41.373
- [quietly]
I'm sorry.

36:43.201 --> 36:45.420
- There's the coward I know.

36:51.470 --> 36:54.429
[spooky music]

36:54.473 --> 36:57.824
♪

36:57.867 --> 37:00.087
[breathing heavily]

37:08.226 --> 37:09.357
- [screams]

37:10.532 --> 37:12.708
[screaming]

37:20.063 --> 37:21.935
- Mmm.

37:24.198 --> 37:26.156
- Just do it already.

37:31.858 --> 37:33.860
- Actually,

37:33.903 --> 37:35.905
I think I have
a better idea.

37:37.211 --> 37:39.735
- [breathing heavily]

37:49.092 --> 37:50.398
[phone chimes]

37:52.531 --> 37:53.532
- What?

37:53.575 --> 37:55.751
What is it?

37:55.795 --> 37:57.100
- They took the hit down.

37:59.668 --> 38:01.670
- Really?

38:01.714 --> 38:02.802
- Why would they do that?

38:04.151 --> 38:06.196
- I have no idea.

38:07.676 --> 38:08.938
- Look.

38:15.945 --> 38:19.122
Is that him?
The guy in the truck?

38:19.166 --> 38:20.515
- Yeah.

38:20.559 --> 38:23.518
[dramatic music]

38:23.562 --> 38:30.569
♪

38:32.310 --> 38:33.746
- Looks like they decided

38:33.789 --> 38:35.661
to take care of business
themselves.

38:51.067 --> 38:52.765
- That was a false hit on Esme.

38:52.808 --> 38:54.854
Strike team couldn't find
any sign of her.

38:54.897 --> 38:57.030
- Oh, it looked like her.
I'm sorry.

38:57.073 --> 38:58.510
I'm just anxious
to bring her in.

38:58.553 --> 38:59.902
It won't happen again.

38:59.946 --> 39:01.948
- No, it's fine.
We'll get her.

39:01.991 --> 39:03.166
They've cleared a bounty.

39:06.518 --> 39:09.521
[motorcycle humming]

39:34.241 --> 39:41.248
♪

39:51.214 --> 39:52.694
- [sighs]

39:53.956 --> 39:55.654
Sorry I'm late.

39:55.697 --> 39:57.177
- Sounds like the Jackals
were right on time.

39:57.220 --> 39:58.700
- Just like we planned.

39:58.744 --> 40:00.310
- We shoulda stuck with you.
You okay?

40:00.354 --> 40:02.661
- Yeah, I'm fine.
Any movement here yet?

40:02.704 --> 40:03.836
- Not yet.

40:03.879 --> 40:06.316
[indistinct chatter]

40:11.887 --> 40:13.585
- Nice truck you got there.

40:14.716 --> 40:15.891
- Ya.
- Yeah.

40:23.421 --> 40:25.684
- Come on,
let's get outta here.

40:31.690 --> 40:33.822
[engine revs]

40:36.608 --> 40:37.913
- There's our target.

40:40.699 --> 40:42.701
[dramatic music]

40:42.744 --> 40:45.094
- Purge prisoner
transport departing.

41:10.119 --> 41:11.773
- Let's go get our boy.
